00:21:24,034 --> 00:21:26,912
But today,
it's me and Gus.

251
00:21:26,995 --> 00:21:29,832
I've never asked you
any other time, okay?

252
00:21:29,957 --> 00:21:31,834
Good.
Glad you agree.

253
00:21:31,959 --> 00:21:34,294
Can't argue about this
right now. Gotta warm up.

254
00:21:38,757 --> 00:21:41,426
I'm sorry. We have
a bit of a delay.

255
00:21:41,510 --> 00:21:43,971
We're correcting a bit
of a maintenance problem.

256
00:21:44,054 --> 00:21:46,974
So we don't have a bit
of a crash?

257
00:21:47,057 --> 00:21:48,976
Is there someplace I can stay? Yes.

258
00:21:49,059 --> 00:21:52,187
The Premiere Lounge is just
down there on your right.

259
00:21:52,312 --> 00:21:54,189
Thanks.

260
00:21:54,314 --> 00:21:56,191
[ Lyons ] When the sun goes
down, it'll actually be...

261
00:21:56,316 --> 00:21:58,235
an easier time to hit
for both teams.

262
00:21:58,360 --> 00:22:00,362
[ Scully ] And now, talkin'about
shadows and sunlight,

263
00:22:00,487 --> 00:22:02,823
that might very well sum up
Billy Chapel.

264
00:22:02,948 --> 00:22:05,450
Long has he stood
in the brilliant sunshine...

265
00:22:05,576 --> 00:22:07,703
in his great, 19-year career.

266
00:22:07,828 --> 00:22:11,665
But now, battling back from
an 8 and 11 record this year,

267
00:22:11,748 --> 00:22:15,878
trying to fiight his way out of
the shadows back into the sunlight.

268
00:22:16,003 --> 00:22:18,672
He'll be facing Mike Robinson,
followed by Jonathan Warble...

269
00:22:18,755 --> 00:22:20,674
and then Sam Tuttle.

270
00:22:20,757 --> 00:22:23,510
Bottom of the fiirst inning, no
score, and the Yankees coming up.

271
00:22:43,989 --> 00:22:46,033
What's he lookin' at?

272
00:22:48,994 --> 00:22:53,165
He's lookin'...
at the clouds.

273
00:22:53,248 --> 00:22:55,167
You okay, Chap?

274
00:22:56,960 --> 00:22:59,755
Chappie!
You okay?

275
00:23:08,013 --> 00:23:11,934
[ Man On P.A.]
Catching, number 27, Gus Sinski.

276
00:23:12,059 --> 00:23:13,936
Number 27.

277
00:23:14,061 --> 00:23:17,397
At shortstop, number 7,
Jose Garcia.

278
00:23:17,523 --> 00:23:20,108
Trying to take my hand off? Sorry.

279
00:23:20,234 --> 00:23:22,694
just let me set for that juice. Warn
me or something. Pitching, number 14,

280
00:23:22,819 --> 00:23:26,281
Billy Chapel. I'm gonna throw a
little harder than usual today.

281
00:23:26,406 --> 00:23:28,283
There's your warning.

282
00:23:28,408 --> 00:23:31,078
Chap, don't throw it away
too early.

283
00:23:34,081 --> 00:23:36,416
Today I'm throwin'
hard, Gus.

284
00:23:38,460 --> 00:23:40,629
You and me?
One more time?

285
00:23:42,548 --> 00:23:44,424
Why not?

286
00:23:48,053 --> 00:23:50,764
[ Cheering ]

287
00:23:56,770 --> 00:24:00,607
[ Man ] Hey, Chapel! We got
you, Chapel! You're done!

288
00:24:00,691 --> 00:24:05,445
We're gonna stick a fork in
you, Chapel! You are finished!

289
00:24:05,529 --> 00:24:09,783
You are complete! The Tigers are
done! You're done! You're finished!

290
00:24:09,867 --> 00:24:11,785
Get outta town!

291
00:24:12,911 --> 00:24:15,414
I can always tell
when I'm in New York.

292
00:24:15,539 --> 00:24:17,708
[ Blowing Horn ]
Hey, Chapel!

293
00:24:17,833 --> 00:24:21,128
Yo, Chapel!
You suck!

294
00:24:22,629 --> 00:24:24,590
You stink on ice!

295
00:24:24,673 --> 00:24:27,009
You couldn't pitch a tent!

296
00:24:28,969 --> 00:24:31,930
[ Shouting, Cheering
Intensifies ]

297
00:24:41,190 --> 00:24:43,859
[ Chapel's Voice ]
Clear the mechanism.

298
00:24:43,984 --> 00:24:45,861
[ Shouting, Cheering
Continues, Muted ]

299
00:24:45,986 --> 00:24:50,657
[ No Audio ]

300
00:24:54,077 --> 00:24:55,996
Hello, Mike.

301
00:25:00,751 --> 00:25:04,379
[ Umpire ]
Strike one!

302
00:25:07,049 --> 00:25:08,967
[ Scully On TV ]
So, Chapel working on Robinson.

303
00:25:09,051 --> 00:25:11,512
Bottom of the fiirst inning.
No score.

304
00:25:14,306 --> 00:25:17,184
And there's a little looper
to Jose Garcia. One away.

305
00:25:18,769 --> 00:25:20,687
Oh, this is-
This is my lucky day.

306
00:25:20,771 --> 00:25:22,814
Hey, how are ya? How you
doin'? Fine. How you doin'?

307
00:25:22,940 --> 00:25:24,858
Uh, the Bud
on the tap is good.

308
00:25:24,942 --> 00:25:26,860
Okay. Oh, this is a beautiful day...

309
00:25:26,944 --> 00:25:28,862
for the big ballpark
in the Bronx.

310
00:25:31,615 --> 00:25:34,493
[ Scully Continues ] He was an
All-American shortstop there,

311
00:25:34,576 --> 00:25:37,371
and he has certainly done
an outstanding job.

312
00:25:37,496 --> 00:25:39,873
Two solid years, and now
a third with the Yankees.

313
00:25:39,957 --> 00:25:41,875
Pretty good breaking ball.
Did get it up...

314
00:25:41,959 --> 00:25:44,878
but got away with it. Lot of guys would
be upset about missin' their flight-

315
00:25:44,962 --> 00:25:48,090
You know, delay, this and that
- but this works out beautiful for me.

316
00:25:50,050 --> 00:25:52,553
[ Scully Continues ] So, Chapel
trying to derail the Yankees,

317
00:25:52,678 --> 00:25:55,180
and the Yankees trying
to end a season...

318
00:25:55,305 --> 00:25:58,183
that has long been finished
by Detroit.

319
00:26:00,853 --> 00:26:02,688
[ Lyons ] Warble had a
game earlier this season...

320
00:26:02,771 --> 00:26:04,731
where he had five hits,
nine R.B.I.s.

321
00:26:04,815 --> 00:26:06,733
That's a week
for a lot of guys.

322
00:26:06,817 --> 00:26:09,778
I don't know. They-They pushed
this guy up to pitch this game.

323
00:26:09,903 --> 00:26:14,449
So, basically we clinch today
and I get to see it. Beautiful.

324
00:26:14,575 --> 00:26:17,077
[ Scully ] They were 63 and
97. The Yankees, meanwhile-

325
00:26:17,202 --> 00:26:20,539
Hi. What can I get for
you? Chivas and water.

326
00:26:20,622 --> 00:26:22,708
[ Bar Patron ] Okay,
here we go. Everything is-

327
00:26:22,791 --> 00:26:25,460
[ Scully ] Good sinker. Oh,
look at that. Ah, it's early.

328
00:26:25,586 --> 00:26:28,714
You got, uh,
nuts, chips, somethin'?

329
00:26:28,797 --> 00:26:31,633
- We got those pretzels.
- I can make do.

330
00:26:31,758 --> 00:26:34,928
Thank you.

331
00:26:35,012 --> 00:26:37,389
[ Scully ] Good fastball
with some movement on it.

332
00:26:37,472 --> 00:26:41,143
And down goes Warble. jesus, he swung
at that? This guy, he's got nothin' now.

333
00:26:41,268 --> 00:26:44,396
If I was Boston, I'd be worried. I'd be,
like, what, are they throwin' the game?

334
00:26:46,481 --> 00:26:48,650
This guy used to be a monster,
to tell you the truth.

335
00:26:48,775 --> 00:26:50,652
When he first came up,
he was unhittable.

336
00:26:50,777 --> 00:26:52,654
Now, he's a junker.

337
00:26:52,779 --> 00:26:55,282
30-30 three years in a row,

338
00:26:55,407 --> 00:26:57,910
and in baseball circles we all know that
there's no love lost between these two guys.

339
00:26:57,993 --> 00:26:59,912
They don't like
each other too much.

340
00:26:59,995 --> 00:27:01,914
[ Cheering ]

341
00:27:01,997 --> 00:27:06,001
[ Man On P.A.] At third
base, number 13, Sam Tuttle.

342
00:27:08,045 --> 00:27:09,963
[ Chapel ]
Sam Tuttle.

343
00:27:10,047 --> 00:27:13,634
I can't think of a better reason
not to be a Yankee.

344
00:27:15,427 --> 00:27:17,804
[ Scully ]
Sam Tuttle hit. 625.

345
00:27:17,888 --> 00:27:20,432
He went 5 for 8
against Chapel this year.

346
00:27:20,516 --> 00:27:22,434
[ Lyons ] That would
make me not like a guy.

347
00:27:22,518 --> 00:27:24,937
[ Scully ]
I would think so.

348
00:27:29,358 --> 00:27:32,611
[ Chanting ]
Tuttle! Tuttle! Tuttle!

349
00:27:32,694 --> 00:27:38,826
Tuttle! Tuttle! Tuttle!

350
00:27:38,951 --> 00:27:41,203
[ Chanting Continues ]

351
00:27:43,872 --> 00:27:46,500
[ Scully ] Fastball on the
inside corner. Strike one.

352
00:27:46,625 --> 00:27:49,336
Wasn't that inside?

353
00:27:49,461 --> 00:27:52,130
You never do swing at the
fiirst pitch, do you, Sam?

354
00:27:59,888 --> 00:28:02,140
No, no,
we're off the page now, Gus.

355
00:28:02,224 --> 00:28:05,644
This is between me and ugly.

356
00:28:05,727 --> 00:28:07,646
Straight heat.

357
00:28:07,729 --> 00:28:09,648
That a boy.

358
00:28:11,817 --> 00:28:14,862
- Strike two!
- Aw, that shit's outside.

359
00:28:16,113 --> 00:28:18,657
No wonder nobody
likes you, Tuttle.

360
00:28:18,740 --> 00:28:21,034
Everything's a goddamn
debate. [ Scully ] Fastball,

361
00:28:21,118 --> 00:28:23,662
and it runs
right on that outside corner.

362
00:28:23,745 --> 00:28:26,373
So 0 and 2 the count
to Sam Tuttle.

363
00:28:26,498 --> 00:28:30,711
I saw that shitty little
Hollywood movie you did.

364
00:28:37,593 --> 00:28:39,553
Ball! [ Lyons ] Gus
Sinski wanted that one.

365
00:28:39,678 --> 00:28:43,515
So did Chappie. You see
the reaction on his face.

366
00:28:43,599 --> 00:28:45,726
That's a pretty good pitch
on the outside corner.

367
00:28:45,851 --> 00:28:49,396
Tuttle didn't like the first two calls, and
now he gets a break on that outside corner.

368
00:28:49,521 --> 00:28:53,734
That's not the kind of pitch Chapel's
gonna like being called a ball all day long.

369
00:28:58,614 --> 00:29:03,452
Don't crowd me, Sam.
I hate being crowded.

370
00:29:05,704 --> 00:29:08,207
No.

371
00:29:08,332 --> 00:29:11,877
So, 1 and 2 the count, and whoops,
Tuttle has really moved up on the plate.

372
00:29:12,002 --> 00:29:14,880
He's all over the plate
right now.

373
00:29:20,010 --> 00:29:22,721
Now you got the idea.

374
00:29:27,184 --> 00:29:29,436
[ Scully ] Uh-oh! Down goes
Tuttle. [ Fans Protesting ]

375
00:29:29,520 --> 00:29:32,439
What a knockdown pitch that was.
There's a message being delivered.

376
00:29:32,523 --> 00:29:34,775
Yankee Stadium
is like a schoolyard,

377
00:29:34,858 --> 00:29:38,612
and Bill Murdie looks like
a teacher who sees trouble.

378
00:29:38,737 --> 00:29:41,240
You know, they say
in every great athlete...

379
00:29:41,365 --> 00:29:44,076
there's a mean streak,
and Billy Chapel's no different.

380
00:29:44,159 --> 00:29:47,412
[ Scully ] Bill Murdie
goes from umpire to referee.

381
00:29:47,496 --> 00:29:49,832
[ Lyons ] Anytime I
played against this guy,

382
00:29:49,957 --> 00:29:53,335
if he felt like he had his good
stuff, he'd flip you like this.

383
00:29:53,460 --> 00:29:56,004
Throw a ball right up there over
your head just to let you know that,

384
00:29:56,129 --> 00:29:58,423
"I can throw the ball
anywhere I want today-"

385
00:29:58,507 --> 00:30:00,843
[ Bar Patron ] You know, I've
been a Yankee fan since 1958.

386
00:30:00,968 --> 00:30:06,139
- I can name a Yankee for every number.
- Oh, God. Please don't.

387
00:30:06,223 --> 00:30:08,642
Number one:
Billy Martin, Bobby Richardson.

388
00:30:08,767 --> 00:30:12,604
Number two: Frank "The Crow"
Crosetti and Bobby Murcer.

389
00:30:12,688 --> 00:30:15,983
Number three.. the Babe. Number
four.. Gehrig. Five.. DiMaggio.

390
00:30:16,108 --> 00:30:19,319
Six.. Steve Boyer, Roy White.
Excuse me. Would you mind?

391
00:30:22,072 --> 00:30:25,450
You can't smoke in a bar. What,
now you can't talk in a bar?

392
00:30:25,534 --> 00:30:27,494
This ain't church, lady.
[ Scoffs ]

393
00:30:27,578 --> 00:30:30,622
[ Scully ] Tuttle back up to
the plate. [ Umpire ] 2 and 2!

394
00:30:30,747 --> 00:30:32,875
Same shit,
different day, huh?

395
00:30:33,000 --> 00:30:35,169
I'd throw it at you again,

396
00:30:35,252 --> 00:30:37,171
but I'm afraid
Murdie'd run me.

397
00:30:41,675 --> 00:30:43,552
Strike three!

398
00:30:43,677 --> 00:30:46,263
[ Scully ] Oh, good breaking
ball. Got him looking.

399
00:30:46,346 --> 00:30:49,474
[ Lyons ] What a great job of settin'up
a hitter. Let's take another look.

400
00:30:49,600 --> 00:30:53,645
Tuttle looks like a deer caught in the
headlights. Chapel just jelly-legged him.

401
00:30:53,770 --> 00:30:57,024
[ Scully ] So at the end of one,
Tigers nothing, Yankees nothing.

402
00:30:57,149 --> 00:31:01,278
All right, here we go now. Four,
fiive, six. Let's get something started.

403
00:31:01,361 --> 00:31:03,405
jose, attababy.

404
00:31:03,530 --> 00:31:06,200
It's all about
positioning, right?

405
00:31:06,283 --> 00:31:08,202
You gotta wait on this guy,
all right?

406
00:31:08,285 --> 00:31:10,329
Hey, Mike? Some water? [ Man ] Yeah?

407
00:31:10,454 --> 00:31:13,081
Sure thing, Billy.
You all right?

408
00:31:16,710 --> 00:31:18,795
You got it goin' good
out there.

409
00:31:20,088 --> 00:31:22,883
Make sure
you save something.

410
00:31:28,096 --> 00:31:30,307
Birch wants
to play golf tomorrow.

411
00:31:34,353 --> 00:31:37,231
You know, I played golf with
Birch the day I met Jane.

412
00:31:39,274 --> 00:31:41,193
You doin' all right?

413
00:31:42,778 --> 00:31:45,572
Yeah.

414
00:31:45,697 --> 00:31:48,283
I'm not hearin' 'em
at all out there.

415
00:32:03,090 --> 00:32:06,802
[ Car Stereo ] Are you
gathering up the tears

416
00:32:06,927 --> 00:32:10,013
Have you had enough of mine

417
00:32:10,138 --> 00:32:13,934
Are you reelin'in
the years

418
00:32:14,059 --> 00:32:16,436
Stowin'away the time
[ Yells ]

419
00:32:16,520 --> 00:32:20,232
- Ooh. Hot.
- Stupid piece of crap!

420
00:32:20,315 --> 00:32:23,610
Yeah, that'll fiix it.

421
00:32:23,694 --> 00:32:25,946
[ Fades ]

422
00:32:26,071 --> 00:32:29,116
[ Sets Parking Brake ]

423
00:32:32,619 --> 00:32:34,496
[ Shuts Engine Off ]

424
00:32:48,177 --> 00:32:50,095
[ Sighs ]

425
00:32:50,179 --> 00:32:52,848
I don't need any help.

426
00:32:55,767 --> 00:32:58,145
I can see that.
I can see you got your car...

427
00:32:58,228 --> 00:33:00,647
kicked completely
into submission.

428
00:33:00,731 --> 00:33:03,275
I mean it.
just go away.

429
00:33:03,358 --> 00:33:08,030
[ Sighs ] You know, I can
always tell when I'm in New York.

430
00:33:10,449 --> 00:33:12,743
Do you really know
anything about cars?

431
00:33:19,333 --> 00:33:22,628
[ Chuckles ] You want
me to have a look at it?

432
00:33:22,711 --> 00:33:24,630
Okay.
It's not mine.

433
00:33:24,713 --> 00:33:26,632
It's just a trashy rental.

434
00:33:26,715 --> 00:33:28,842
Yeah. Mine too.

435
00:33:34,681 --> 00:33:37,351
Why don't you try the key?
See if we can't get it started.

436
00:33:40,771 --> 00:33:42,689
[ Ignition Cranking ]

437
00:33:42,773 --> 00:33:45,192
[ Chapel ] Should've paid
attention in auto shop.

438
00:33:45,275 --> 00:33:47,694
Um-

439
00:33:47,820 --> 00:33:51,198
[ Ignition Cranking ]

440
00:33:56,620 --> 00:34:00,040
- [ Engine Starts ]
- [ Laughing ]

441
00:34:00,165 --> 00:34:02,459
What did you do?
Well, I was-

442
00:34:02,543 --> 00:34:05,796
I have no idea. I-
I don't- [ Chuckles ]

443
00:34:05,879 --> 00:34:10,551
I don't know anything about cars.
I was just trying to be manly.

444
00:34:10,634 --> 00:34:13,262
Well, that was great.
Thank you.

445
00:34:13,387 --> 00:34:16,014
You saved my day.
Of course I did.

446
00:34:16,098 --> 00:34:19,893
I said I would.
Where are you headed?

447
00:34:20,018 --> 00:34:24,439
I'm not sure.
Bear Mountain, maybe.

448
00:34:24,565 --> 00:34:27,776
I just threw my stuff in the car and
took off. Had to get out of the city.

449
00:34:27,901 --> 00:34:30,737
How come? 'Cause summer's
over and I missed it.

450
00:34:30,821 --> 00:34:35,742
You know, I work all the time.
Makes me feel old. I don't know.

451
00:34:40,706 --> 00:34:42,583
Oh.

452
00:34:43,959 --> 00:34:46,295
Well, thanks again.

453
00:34:51,091 --> 00:34:54,511
So, what's the problem? My
problem seems to be solved.

454
00:34:54,595 --> 00:34:58,515
Oh, no. Well, wait a
sec. No, the car's fiine.

455
00:34:58,599 --> 00:35:02,936
But listen, honey, I gave up on four
calls haulin' my ass out to you, okay?

456
00:35:03,061 --> 00:35:06,315
That's 100 bucks to me. So if there's
nothin' wrong with this car now,

457
00:35:06,440 --> 00:35:09,484
there will be when I bring it
down to the city, okay? The car's-

458
00:35:09,610 --> 00:35:12,321
- Everything all right?
- [ Man ] Everything's peaches, mac.

459
00:35:19,244 --> 00:35:21,830
You're-
You're Billy Chapel.

460
00:35:21,955 --> 00:35:24,791
I can't believe it.
It's a pleasure to meet you.

461
00:35:24,875 --> 00:35:28,921
I can't believe this.
Oh, I'm sorry.

462
00:35:29,046 --> 00:35:31,340
[ Tow Truck Radio Chattering,
Indistinct ]

463
00:35:31,465 --> 00:35:34,176
You know, you are the greatest
freakin' ballplayer out there.

464
00:35:34,301 --> 00:35:36,261
I'm sor- I'm sorry.
But you really are.

465
00:35:36,386 --> 00:35:40,307
I'm gonna go get that.
You stay right here, okay?

466
00:35:42,059 --> 00:35:43,810
[ Car Door Opens ]
Billy Chapel.

467
00:35:43,936 --> 00:35:46,772
Nice to meet you.
jane Aubrey.

468
00:35:48,982 --> 00:35:51,443
You know, I-
I got this problem.

469
00:35:51,568 --> 00:35:54,863
See, um, I'd like
to keep talkin' with you,

470
00:35:54,988 --> 00:35:57,449
but I gotta go to work.

471
00:36:00,536 --> 00:36:02,371
[ Chuckling ] just a second. Hey.

472
00:36:02,496 --> 00:36:04,373
[ Whistles ]

473
00:36:04,498 --> 00:36:06,667
I'll get there
when I get there.

474
00:36:06,792 --> 00:36:08,919
Can you do me a favor?
Anything.

475
00:36:09,002 --> 00:36:10,921
We got a bum deal
on this rental here,

476
00:36:11,004 --> 00:36:14,591
so if you could
- if you could haul this back to town for us,

477
00:36:14,675 --> 00:36:17,469
I'd really appreciate it.
I can't take that.

478
00:36:17,553 --> 00:36:20,472
Wait a sec. Wait a sec.
What are you doing?

479
00:36:21,598 --> 00:36:23,767
You like baseball?
What?

480
00:36:23,851 --> 00:36:26,186
Baseball. [ Clattering
] No, not really. Hey!

481
00:36:26,270 --> 00:36:29,022
- You ever been?
