01:12:09,121 --> 01:12:11,039
And me.

960
01:12:14,543 --> 01:12:17,629
I was really
thinking about...

961
01:12:17,754 --> 01:12:21,383
how nice it would be
to spend time together.

962
01:12:32,895 --> 01:12:34,771
Yeah.

963
01:12:34,897 --> 01:12:36,773
[ All Shouting,
Indistinct ]

964
01:13:00,088 --> 01:13:03,091
Oh! These are great.

965
01:13:03,217 --> 01:13:05,511
We'll use 'em
in Central Park.

966
01:13:05,636 --> 01:13:08,055
No, we can
use 'em out here.

967
01:13:13,393 --> 01:13:16,063
You ever gotten
your heart broken?

968
01:13:16,146 --> 01:13:20,984
Yeah, when we lost
the pennant in '87.

969
01:13:25,989 --> 01:13:28,992
Would you still love me
if I got burned in a fiire?

970
01:13:29,076 --> 01:13:30,953
Oh!
[ Laughs ]

971
01:13:31,078 --> 01:13:36,166
Yes. If I ran into a
tree and got paralyzed?

972
01:13:38,043 --> 01:13:39,962
[ Scoffs ]

973
01:13:41,213 --> 01:13:43,799
Yes.

974
01:13:43,924 --> 01:13:46,844
What If I were
totally disfiigured,

975
01:13:46,969 --> 01:13:49,138
if my face were
all scraped away,

976
01:13:49,221 --> 01:13:52,474
I had no arms, no legs,
no brain waves...

977
01:13:52,599 --> 01:13:54,977
and I was being kept alive
on a heart-lung machine.

978
01:13:55,102 --> 01:13:56,979
Would you love me?

979
01:13:57,104 --> 01:13:59,148
No.
[ Laughing ]

980
01:13:59,273 --> 01:14:02,693
But we could still
be friends though.

981
01:14:02,818 --> 01:14:04,695
[ Chuckling ]

982
01:14:07,656 --> 01:14:09,700
Do you believe in God?

983
01:14:12,828 --> 01:14:14,705
[ Whispers ]
Yes.

984
01:14:16,039 --> 01:14:19,001
How old do you think you're
gonna be when you die?

985
01:14:24,339 --> 01:14:26,383
Do you like
white meat or dark?

986
01:14:28,844 --> 01:14:30,929
Dark.

987
01:14:31,054 --> 01:14:32,931
Dark?

988
01:14:33,056 --> 01:14:37,144
The dark part's more fatty,
but it's cool to like that part.

989
01:14:37,227 --> 01:14:40,522
You like it chopped up?

990
01:14:40,606 --> 01:14:43,609
You know how people dice
it in the chef salad,

991
01:14:43,734 --> 01:14:45,611
or you like it torn?

992
01:14:45,736 --> 01:14:47,821
I personally
like it torn.

993
01:14:47,905 --> 01:14:50,324
Not that you have to
like it how I like it.

994
01:15:02,753 --> 01:15:04,671
No questions.

995
01:15:17,309 --> 01:15:19,645
[ Chapel ] Why you
askin'me all this stuff?

996
01:15:19,770 --> 01:15:21,814
[ Jane ]
Because I want to know you.

997
01:15:25,275 --> 01:15:29,655
Breaking ball, a comeback right at
Billy Chapel to hold onto the line drive.

998
01:15:29,780 --> 01:15:32,991
- [ Cheering ] - [ Lyons ] This is
one of those chuck-and-duck pitches.

999
01:15:33,116 --> 01:15:36,411
When you throw a ball like that
and it comes back at you that quick,

1000
01:15:36,537 --> 01:15:38,413
it's almost like
the ball catches you.

1001
01:15:38,539 --> 01:15:40,958
[ Scully ] So far, Chapel
is gettin'away with it.

1002
01:15:41,083 --> 01:15:43,460
[ All Chanting ]
Go, Tigers, go, Tigers.

1003
01:15:43,585 --> 01:15:46,547
Hey, ho, hey, ho.

1004
01:15:47,631 --> 01:15:51,009
[ No Audible Dialogue ]

1005
01:16:11,989 --> 01:16:14,116
[ Scully ] We have one out here
in the top of the sixth inning.

1006
01:16:14,241 --> 01:16:18,245
No score. Spellman has allowed
two hits. Chapel has been perfect.

1007
01:16:18,370 --> 01:16:20,831
The batter is
Gus Sinski, 0 for 1.

1008
01:16:20,956 --> 01:16:24,168
[ Lyons ] Gus has had a tough
year this year at the plate,

1009
01:16:24,293 --> 01:16:26,587
but they really pay him for
what he does behind the plate.

1010
01:16:26,670 --> 01:16:30,132
He handles his pitching staff so well,
and any kind of hit that he gets...

1011
01:16:30,215 --> 01:16:32,467
is a bonus for this club.

1012
01:16:32,551 --> 01:16:35,095
- [ Crowd Cheering ]
- Yes!

1013
01:16:37,014 --> 01:16:42,394
- Simon Louis'a little slow in coming up with it.
- Get down! Get down!

1014
01:16:42,519 --> 01:16:45,230
Safe!
It wasn't close!

1015
01:16:45,355 --> 01:16:47,733
He beat the play!

1016
01:16:47,816 --> 01:16:49,735
Good call.

1017
01:16:53,363 --> 01:16:55,240
Attaboy!

1018
01:16:58,202 --> 01:17:01,788
In a game like this,
that could be a huge play.

1019
01:17:01,872 --> 01:17:06,502
The last leg double Sinski had was
during the Reagan administration.

1020
01:17:06,585 --> 01:17:09,588
The Yankees are now on the
phone talking to the bullpen...

1021
01:17:09,713 --> 01:17:12,007
and they get
a left-hander up.

1022
01:17:12,132 --> 01:17:14,510
Bobby Mack is ticked off
with the Yankees,

1023
01:17:14,635 --> 01:17:19,139
and he gives batter Jose Garcia
the intentional walk.

1024
01:17:19,223 --> 01:17:23,977
In a moment there'll be runners at first
and second, one out in the sixth, no score...

1025
01:17:24,061 --> 01:17:28,065
and a left-handed hitter coming
up- that would be Brian Whitt.

1026
01:17:35,197 --> 01:17:37,074
[ Whirring ]

1027
01:18:05,269 --> 01:18:07,563
[ Chapel ]
Jane.

1028
01:18:07,646 --> 01:18:10,399
I was just
lookin' for you.

1029
01:18:10,482 --> 01:18:12,401
Billy?

1030
01:18:13,527 --> 01:18:15,404
Oh, my God.

1031
01:18:18,407 --> 01:18:20,868
Can't feel
anything.

1032
01:18:20,993 --> 01:18:25,497
Hold this. Close your fiingers
around it. Hold it up. Hold it up.

1033
01:18:28,500 --> 01:18:32,045
[ Tires Screech ]

1034
01:18:34,464 --> 01:18:37,301
Hold on, Billy.

1035
01:18:42,306 --> 01:18:45,601
- [ Woman ] Occupation?
- Pitcher. He's hurt his hand.

1036
01:18:45,726 --> 01:18:47,936
- We need a doctor.
- Are you his wife?

1037
01:18:48,020 --> 01:18:50,189
No. No.
Are you a relative?

1038
01:18:50,314 --> 01:18:53,484
Then I'll have to ask you
to wait outside.

1039
01:18:53,609 --> 01:18:55,486
jane.

1040
01:18:55,611 --> 01:18:58,780
My friend cut his hand.
It's bleeding very deeply.

1041
01:18:58,864 --> 01:19:01,366
- Ma'am.
- Please, we need help.

1042
01:19:03,911 --> 01:19:06,914
Is this not America?

1043
01:19:06,997 --> 01:19:10,876
Is baseball not America's
favorite pastime?

1044
01:19:12,294 --> 01:19:15,005
- Can I help you?
- Are you a doctor?

1045
01:19:15,130 --> 01:19:18,926
- Yes.
- Thank you, God.

1046
01:19:23,347 --> 01:19:25,849
jane.
I'm right here.

1047
01:19:25,974 --> 01:19:28,519
- Jane, call Mike Udall.
- What?

1048
01:19:28,644 --> 01:19:32,314
The trainer in Detroit. Call
him. Tell him what happened.

1049
01:19:32,439 --> 01:19:36,235
I'm going with you. Sorry, there's
not enough room in the Medivac.

1050
01:19:36,360 --> 01:19:39,154
You're gonna need
to stay here.

1051
01:19:45,035 --> 01:19:46,995
jane!

1052
01:19:49,581 --> 01:19:52,751
Call Mike. He's the most
important person for me right now.

1053
01:19:59,258 --> 01:20:01,301
You need to clear out.

1054
01:20:27,953 --> 01:20:31,248
- [ Bat Cracks ]
- [ Scully ] There's a little flare just by Howell's glove...

1055
01:20:31,373 --> 01:20:33,333
- into right field.
- [ Players Shouting, Indistinct ]

1056
01:20:33,458 --> 01:20:36,795
Here comes Sinski.
Colborn waves him to the plate.

1057
01:20:36,920 --> 01:20:40,048
- The throw. He is... in there!
- Safe! Safe!

1058
01:20:40,132 --> 01:20:42,634
- [ Groans ] - The Tigers
take a 1-to-nothing lead.

1059
01:20:42,759 --> 01:20:46,972
[ Lyons ] What a great slide by Sinski,
sliding away from the play at the plate.

1060
01:20:47,055 --> 01:20:50,017
Jim Colborn, the third base
coach, didn't even hesitate.

1061
01:20:50,100 --> 01:20:52,936
Your catcher, the slowest guy
on your team, comin'around third,

1062
01:20:53,061 --> 01:20:57,858
trying to score in a scoreless ball game, had
no hesitation at all, sent him all the way-

1063
01:20:57,941 --> 01:21:00,319
[ Continues, Indistinct ]

1064
01:21:00,444 --> 01:21:02,779
[ Man ] It's all bullshit,
Billy. Don't listen to it.

1065
01:21:02,905 --> 01:21:07,201
You've done it all. You've won
every award there is to win.

1066
01:21:07,284 --> 01:21:09,912
You got a room reserved
at Cooperstown, Billy.

1067
01:21:10,037 --> 01:21:13,123
I just don't know how much more
you have to prove.

1068
01:21:13,248 --> 01:21:18,962
Even if you do come back, you're not gonna be
a hundred percent. You may not even be fifty.

1069
01:21:19,087 --> 01:21:22,925
- [ Chapel ] What'd you say?
- Nothin'. Let's knock off for the day. Jane's here.

1070
01:21:23,008 --> 01:21:25,052
What'd you say?
I didn't say anything.

1071
01:21:25,177 --> 01:21:27,262
You said "if. "
I didn't mean "if. "

1072
01:21:27,387 --> 01:21:29,765
But you said "if. "
I only meant-

1073
01:21:29,848 --> 01:21:32,726
Think I'm not comin' back? Billy.

1074
01:21:32,810 --> 01:21:35,562
Say it. You're tired. Let's quit.

1075
01:21:35,646 --> 01:21:38,816
Say it, chickenshit.

1076
01:21:38,941 --> 01:21:43,529
You got a job. That's to get
me strong and get me back.

1077
01:21:43,654 --> 01:21:46,073
All right?
You get me back...

1078
01:21:46,156 --> 01:21:48,617
I'll fiigure out how to win.

1079
01:21:52,788 --> 01:21:56,583
You wanna work with me tomorrow,
then get your mind right.

1080
01:21:56,667 --> 01:21:59,253
You get it right,
or you don't come around me.

1081
01:21:59,378 --> 01:22:01,380
[ Jane ]
You mad at me or at Mike?

1082
01:22:01,505 --> 01:22:03,465
[ Chapel ]
Why would I be mad at Mike?

1083
01:22:03,590 --> 01:22:05,968
You practically tore
his head off. Talk to me.

1084
01:22:06,093 --> 01:22:08,303
Talk?
You don't want to talk.

1085
01:22:08,428 --> 01:22:12,975
You just want to give me your
version of why I should quit.

1086
01:22:13,100 --> 01:22:15,978
- I want this shit outta here.
- What're you tryin' to do?

1087
01:22:19,857 --> 01:22:23,610
Are you trying to make me mad? Are you
gonna pack up my things and make me go...

1088
01:22:23,694 --> 01:22:26,155
so you can sit here in the dark
and feel sorry for yourself?

1089
01:22:26,238 --> 01:22:30,576
Well, forget it, Billy. You
can't cook, you can't drive-

1090
01:22:36,707 --> 01:22:39,042
I'll hire somebody
to drive me.

1091
01:22:41,295 --> 01:22:45,841
Someone who doesn't talk?
Doesn't think bad thoughts?

1092
01:22:45,966 --> 01:22:50,345
Billy, we are gonna get through
this. You just have to try-

1093
01:22:50,429 --> 01:22:53,056
Try! Goddamn it, jane, I'm the
only one who is trying here.

1094
01:22:53,182 --> 01:22:57,603
I got nobody in the front
offiice, nobody in the press...

1095
01:22:57,728 --> 01:23:00,022
and now I got nobody
in this house...

1096
01:23:00,147 --> 01:23:03,442
that thinks
I'm gonna make it back.

1097
01:23:03,525 --> 01:23:06,028
I have been nothing
but supportive of you.

1098
01:23:06,111 --> 01:23:08,363
I don't want you here,
jane! I mean-

1099
01:23:09,615 --> 01:23:11,533
Don't you get it?

1100
01:23:14,161 --> 01:23:17,956
You make
- You make me feel distracted.

1101
01:23:19,917 --> 01:23:22,002
You make me feel weak.

1102
01:23:43,649 --> 01:23:47,402
Billy,
you taught me something.

1103
01:23:47,486 --> 01:23:49,613
You taught me
how to believe again,

1104
01:23:49,738 --> 01:23:53,575
how good things can happen
and that they will happen.

1105
01:23:53,700 --> 01:23:57,246
But now you need to let me teach
you something about what I know-

1106
01:23:57,371 --> 01:24:01,291
about how sometimes life seems
like it's slamming you down,

1107
01:24:01,416 --> 01:24:05,003
but it's really
giving you a gift.

1108
01:24:05,128 --> 01:24:08,257
I had a baby
when I was 16.

1109
01:24:08,340 --> 01:24:10,801
That could've
wrecked me.

1110
01:24:10,926 --> 01:24:15,597
But it didn't. Instead, it was the
best thing that ever happened to me.

1111
01:24:18,433 --> 01:24:22,187
You mean if life gives you
lemons, you make lemonade?

1112
01:24:24,648 --> 01:24:28,861
- You are such an asshole. - If you're tellin'
me I'm never gonna hold that ball again-

1113
01:24:33,907 --> 01:24:35,784
I can't.

1114
01:24:37,077 --> 01:24:39,371
Haven't you ever loved
anything that much?

1115
01:24:45,711 --> 01:24:50,090
I'll call the airlines. See
what kind of flights I can make.

1116
01:24:53,469 --> 01:24:55,387
You do that.

1117
01:24:55,471 --> 01:24:57,389
[ Crowd Cheering ]

1118
01:24:57,473 --> 01:24:59,391
[ Indistinct Chanting ]

1119
01:25:05,481 --> 01:25:07,357
[ Grunts ]

1120
01:25:07,483 --> 01:25:10,861
- Strike!
- [ Scully ] Uh-oh.

1121
01:25:10,986 --> 01:25:13,697
Something happen
to Chapel?

1122
01:25:13,822 --> 01:25:18,577
Frank Perry is on the steps of the dugout
and apparently didn't like what he saw.

1123
01:25:18,660 --> 01:25:21,622
Gimme the ball.

1124
01:25:21,705 --> 01:25:24,291
What are you lookin'-
Gimme the ball.

1125
01:25:25,834 --> 01:25:28,420
just stay there.

1126
01:25:28,504 --> 01:25:31,048
[ Crowd Cheering,
Whistling ]

1127
01:25:31,173 --> 01:25:35,052
[ Lyons ] There's something wrong with either
his arm, his elbow or his shoulder there.

1128
01:25:35,177 --> 01:25:37,971
He doesn't look
very comfortable.

1129
01:25:38,055 --> 01:25:41,517
- Bill, he's hurt.
- [ Scully ] Here he comes. He's goin'out to visit.

1130
01:25:41,600 --> 01:25:43,644
[ Booing ]

1131
01:25:45,979 --> 01:25:48,398
You just do somethin'there? No.

1132
01:25:48,524 --> 01:25:50,859
You hurtin'?
No.

1133
01:25:50,943 --> 01:25:53,695
Uh-huh.
How long?

1134
01:25:55,030 --> 01:25:58,659
- Ten years.
- [ Sighs ]

1135
01:25:58,742 --> 01:26:01,370
What do you wanna do? I'd
like you to smile at me,

1136
01:26:01,453 --> 01:26:04,414
pat me on the fanny, march your
butt to that dugout and sit down.

1137
01:26:04,540 --> 01:26:06,917
- That's what I'd like.
- I want this goddamn game, Billy.

1138
01:26:07,042 --> 01:26:09,086
Well, I want it too.

1139
01:26:15,175 --> 01:26:17,052
[ Exhales Sharply ]

1140
01:26:18,887 --> 01:26:21,098
If it gets any worse,
I'll sit down.

1141
01:26:22,891 --> 01:26:25,102
Ready to go?

1142
01:26:31,275 --> 01:26:33,193
Where's my pat?

1143
01:26:36,405 --> 01:26:38,282
[ Pats ]
Thank you.

1144
01:26:38,407 --> 01:26:41,034
You let me know. Yeah. He's all right.

1145
01:26:42,661 --> 01:26:44,705
[ Jane ]
He's flexing his hand.

1146
01:26:44,830 --> 01:26:48,500
What? He does that
when his arm's tingling.

1147
01:26:48,584 --> 01:26:51,670
Pretty soon he's not gonna be able
to feel anything. Do you know him?

1148
01:26:53,839 --> 01:26:55,966
Yeah, and I know
Mickey fuckin' Mantle.

1149
01:26:56,091 --> 01:26:58,469
[ Bartender ] Hey, watch the
language. There's people in here.

1150
01:26:58,594 --> 01:27:01,054
[ Patrons.. Mocking Laughter ] [ Man On
P.A.] This is a boarding announcement for...

1151
01:27:01,180 --> 01:27:04,808
flight number 12.
God, I hate Yankee fans.

1152
01:27:04,933 --> 01:27:07,060
Hey, you leavin'? How can you
leave when your guy's winnin'?

1153
01:27:07,144 --> 01:27:10,230
He's not gonna win.
How do you know?

1154
01:27:10,314 --> 01:27:14,067
Because he's hurting and he won't
tell anyone and he won't come out.

1155
01:27:14,151 --> 01:27:17,029
[ P.A. Continues,
Indistinct ] I don't know.

1156
01:27:17,154 --> 01:27:19,198
Honey,
I hope you're wrong.

1157
01:27:19,323 --> 01:27:21,366
[ Scully ]
As you mentioned earlier,

1158
01:27:21,450 --> 01:27:24,620
there's no love lost at all
between Tuttle and Chapel.

1159
01:27:24,745 --> 01:27:27,998
Tuttle would just love to break
up this perfecto right now.

1160
01:27:28,123 --> 01:27:30,167
[ Lyons ]
Yes, he would.

1161
01:27:36,298 --> 01:27:41,386
[ Scully ] He bunts up along third. Down
to get it. Backhanded by Chapel to first.

1162
01:27:41,470 --> 01:27:43,555
- You're out!
- And got him!

1163
01:27:43,639 --> 01:27:46,558
[ Groans ] What are you buntin' for,
Tuttle? We need a hit, you pansy!

1164
01:27:46,642 --> 01:27:49,478
[ Scully ]
For the third time today...

1165
01:27:49,561 --> 01:27:51,814
Sam Tuttle has boiled over,

1166
01:27:51,897 --> 01:27:54,691
arguing now with
first base umpire Richie Garcia.

1167
01:27:54,817 --> 01:27:56,985
[ Indistinct Arguing ]

1168
01:27:57,069 --> 01:28:00,030
- Take another look at it.
- [ Lyons ] The only guy that can fiield this ball is Chapel.

1169
01:28:00,155 --> 01:28:02,324
He's like a cat off the mound.

1170
01:28:02,449 --> 01:28:04,660
He slides, picks up the ball
and throws it.

1171
01:28:04,785 --> 01:28:07,830
That enabled him to get up
quicker than just bend over.

1172
01:28:33,230 --> 01:28:37,276
[ Scully ] What a mix we have
goin'on for the last two innings.

1173
01:28:37,401 --> 01:28:40,487
Sitting alone upstairs,
owner Gary Wheeler...

1174
01:28:40,612 --> 01:28:44,408
reportedly has already sold
his ball club, the Tigers,

1175
01:28:44,533 --> 01:28:47,661
to the corporate group
in the box to his left.

1176
01:28:47,744 --> 01:28:51,456
Now an unconfirmed report
beginning to ripple the water...

1177
01:28:51,540 --> 01:28:53,625
that the corporate's
first business...

1178
01:28:53,709 --> 01:28:57,337
would be to trade Billy Chapel
when the season is over.

1179
01:28:57,462 --> 01:29:01,258
So as so often happens in a ball game,
there are so many other undercurrents,

1180
01:29:01,383 --> 01:29:04,428
so many more things
than meet the eye.

1181
01:29:04,553 --> 01:29:06,930
And here we have it all.. [
Male Vocalist, Indistinct ]

1182
01:29:07,055 --> 01:29:09,391
a beleaguered owner selling
a ball club,

1183
01:29:09,475 --> 01:29:12,352
perhaps the new owners selling
the biggest star on the club,

1184
01:29:12,436 --> 01:29:15,522
and all the while,
Billy Chapel, perhaps,

1185
01:29:15,647 --> 01:29:18,066
trying to make
