Well, not so good really,
but, uh, it's almost over now.

1422
01:46:11,788 --> 01:46:16,210
How's your mom? [ Girl
] Heather! Hurry up.

1423
01:46:16,293 --> 01:46:18,670
She's good.
She's really good.

1424
01:46:18,754 --> 01:46:20,422
Heather!

1425
01:46:23,258 --> 01:46:25,761
Go.

1426
01:46:25,844 --> 01:46:29,973
I miss you.

1427
01:46:30,098 --> 01:46:34,561
I miss you too.

1428
01:46:37,272 --> 01:46:41,401
Like you did the day before

1429
01:46:41,527 --> 01:46:44,780
You don't have plans, do
you? [ Jane ] No, I don't.

1430
01:46:44,863 --> 01:46:50,369
Well, I'm gonna be there, and
it's been a while. A long time.

1431
01:46:50,452 --> 01:46:55,249
just thought dinner at the
Waldorf might be nice. About 6:00?

1432
01:46:55,332 --> 01:46:59,294
How about 8:00, your room? Even better.

1433
01:46:59,419 --> 01:47:01,588
Great. I'll see you then.

1434
01:47:04,466 --> 01:47:06,802
Mmm-hmm-hmm

1435
01:47:08,595 --> 01:47:12,015
Oh, no, oh, yeah

1436
01:47:12,141 --> 01:47:15,727
What can I say

1437
01:47:15,811 --> 01:47:19,189
What can I do

1438
01:47:19,314 --> 01:47:22,943
I'm still in love

1439
01:47:23,068 --> 01:47:27,990
So why aren't you

1440
01:47:32,661 --> 01:47:36,623
It don't matter to the moon

1441
01:47:40,836 --> 01:47:44,173
If you're not in my life

1442
01:47:48,886 --> 01:47:52,806
I knew it the day I fiirst
met you fiive years ago.

1443
01:47:52,890 --> 01:47:56,810
What? I've always known
it. You don't need me.

1444
01:47:56,894 --> 01:48:00,939
You and the ball and
the diamond, you're perfect.

1445
01:48:01,023 --> 01:48:03,233
You're a perfectly
beautiful thing.

1446
01:48:03,358 --> 01:48:07,946
You can win or lose the game
all by yourself.

1447
01:48:08,030 --> 01:48:10,407
Oh, babe

1448
01:48:10,532 --> 01:48:13,744
But it matters

1449
01:48:13,869 --> 01:48:17,372
To me

1450
01:48:28,467 --> 01:48:30,594
[ Man ] You feelin'healthy?
You're lookin'good.

1451
01:48:30,719 --> 01:48:32,930
How are you feelin'?
Your shoulder? All right?

1452
01:48:33,055 --> 01:48:35,015
'Cause I'm gonna
keep ya in there.

1453
01:48:35,140 --> 01:48:39,144
[ Crowd Cheering ]

1454
01:49:21,436 --> 01:49:23,355
Mike.

1455
01:49:24,439 --> 01:49:26,942
You all right, Billy?
Yeah.

1456
01:49:27,025 --> 01:49:29,653
Got a pen?
Oh, yeah.

1457
01:49:33,031 --> 01:49:35,450
I want you
to do me a favor.

1458
01:49:35,534 --> 01:49:40,539
I want you to give this
to Wheeler's nephew.

1459
01:49:40,622 --> 01:49:44,793
His nephew? Yeah, that
kid in the clubhouse.

1460
01:49:44,918 --> 01:49:46,795
Oh.

1461
01:49:56,221 --> 01:49:59,308
All right. Let's go, guys. Come on!

1462
01:49:59,433 --> 01:50:01,643
Let's go!

1463
01:50:01,768 --> 01:50:04,855
Let's go, guys. Come on.

1464
01:50:04,980 --> 01:50:07,691
Come on now!
What do ya say?

1465
01:50:07,816 --> 01:50:09,735
Three more!
Come on!

1466
01:50:09,818 --> 01:50:12,863
Nothing but tops out there!

1467
01:50:18,118 --> 01:50:20,329
jesus Christ.

1468
01:50:20,454 --> 01:50:25,918
[ Scully ] Billy Chapel is 40 years old as
he sits in the dugout here at Yankee Stadium.

1469
01:50:26,001 --> 01:50:29,213
Forty years old,
arm weary and aching.

1470
01:50:29,338 --> 01:50:34,551
And don't let anybody tell you
or Billy that life begins at 40.

1471
01:50:34,676 --> 01:50:39,139
4, 100 innings Billy Chapel
has walked to the mound...

1472
01:50:39,223 --> 01:50:41,809
in a brilliant,
19-year career.

1473
01:50:41,892 --> 01:50:46,522
But never before, in all those
years and in all those innings,

1474
01:50:46,647 --> 01:50:51,026
has he ever had a date with
destiny as he has right now.

1475
01:50:51,109 --> 01:50:55,864
He will make the fateful walk to
the loneliest spot in the world,

1476
01:50:55,948 --> 01:51:00,285
the pitching mound at Yankee Stadium
in quest of the pitcher's dream,

1477
01:51:00,369 --> 01:51:03,497
the perfect game.

1478
01:51:23,016 --> 01:51:25,144
Billy Chapel, in quest
of the perfect game.

1479
01:51:25,227 --> 01:51:30,065
You also realize he may very well be
at the crossroads of a brilliant career.

1480
01:51:30,149 --> 01:51:32,818
He's a cinch to wind up
in the Hall of Fame.

1481
01:51:32,901 --> 01:51:36,572
However, after this game,
he has to make the big decision.

1482
01:51:36,697 --> 01:51:39,992
A: Will he continue to do
what has been his life,

1483
01:51:40,075 --> 01:51:42,578
maybe more important
than life itself, baseball?

1484
01:51:42,703 --> 01:51:45,205
Or will he hang it up,
and would a perfect game...

1485
01:51:45,330 --> 01:51:49,001
give him the logical
conclusion to the great career?

1486
01:52:12,941 --> 01:52:16,403
Strout.
You're hitting for Ruiz.

1487
01:52:16,528 --> 01:52:18,739
Grab a bat.

1488
01:52:26,955 --> 01:52:30,083
[ Scully ] At 40 years old,
Billy Chapel is flirting...

1489
01:52:30,167 --> 01:52:33,462
with perhaps the greatest
accomplishment in baseball.

1490
01:52:33,545 --> 01:52:38,300
Standing in his way will be Matt
Crane hitting for Babe Nardini.

1491
01:52:38,383 --> 01:52:40,385
Then Jesus Cabrillo.

1492
01:52:40,469 --> 01:52:43,639
And Ken Strout has a bat
in his hands in the dugout...

1493
01:52:43,764 --> 01:52:48,477
and might very well get
the call to bat for Jaime Ruiz.

1494
01:52:49,978 --> 01:52:52,314
And, you know, Steve, you get
the feeling that Billy Chapel...

1495
01:52:52,439 --> 01:52:55,067
isn't pitching
against left-handers.

1496
01:52:55,150 --> 01:52:57,694
He isn't pitching
against pinch hitters.

1497
01:52:57,820 --> 01:53:00,030
He isn't pitching
against the Yankees.

1498
01:53:00,155 --> 01:53:04,618
He's pitching against time. He's pitching
against the future, against age...

1499
01:53:04,701 --> 01:53:08,497
and, even when you think about
his career, against ending.

1500
01:53:08,622 --> 01:53:13,085
And tonight, I think he might be able to
use that aching old arm one more time...

1501
01:53:13,168 --> 01:53:15,671
to push the sun
back up in the sky...

1502
01:53:15,754 --> 01:53:20,676
and give us
one more day of summer.

1503
01:53:26,974 --> 01:53:30,561
Lord, I know that
I always said...

1504
01:53:30,686 --> 01:53:34,148
that I'd never involve You
in a baseball game.

1505
01:53:34,273 --> 01:53:36,900
It always seemed silly.

1506
01:53:37,025 --> 01:53:39,278
I mean, You got enough to do.

1507
01:53:39,361 --> 01:53:41,280
[ Exhales ]

1508
01:53:41,363 --> 01:53:45,868
But if there's any way You could make
this pain in my shoulder go away...

1509
01:53:45,993 --> 01:53:47,870
for about ten minutes.

1510
01:53:58,505 --> 01:54:01,091
Clear the mechanism.

1511
01:54:01,216 --> 01:54:04,219
[ Cheering Quiets ]

1512
01:54:04,344 --> 01:54:08,056
[ Cheering Increases ]

1513
01:54:08,182 --> 01:54:11,560
[ Feet Stomping ]

1514
01:54:11,643 --> 01:54:15,439
[ Cheering, Stomping
Continue ]

1515
01:54:16,732 --> 01:54:20,402
Clear the mechanism.

1516
01:54:26,742 --> 01:54:30,996
[ Cheering Increases ]

1517
01:54:39,254 --> 01:54:42,883
Okay, okay.

1518
01:54:42,966 --> 01:54:45,135
Three more...

1519
01:54:46,261 --> 01:54:48,180
like I done a million times.

1520
01:55:03,779 --> 01:55:06,865
[ Lyons ] That's tough to come off the bench
and sit and watch eight innings of play...

1521
01:55:06,949 --> 01:55:09,993
and then go up there cold and
have to try and swing the bat.

1522
01:55:10,119 --> 01:55:12,579
But if you don't get your pitch
and hack at it early,

1523
01:55:12,704 --> 01:55:14,623
you might not see one
for the rest of the at bat.

1524
01:55:14,748 --> 01:55:16,917
[ Scully ]
Matt Crane poses quite a threat,

1525
01:55:17,042 --> 01:55:19,878
especially now when Billy
has to be on the ropes.

1526
01:55:19,962 --> 01:55:24,925
No, Gus. A curve
would hurt too much.

1527
01:55:30,055 --> 01:55:34,560
[ Scully ] Ground ball to the right side,
smothered back at third base by Lee Giordano...

1528
01:55:34,643 --> 01:55:36,812
- He's out!
- and throws him out!

1529
01:55:36,937 --> 01:55:40,858
[ Scully ] That would
be another brilliant play.

1530
01:55:40,983 --> 01:55:43,193
No! He beat it!

1531
01:55:52,494 --> 01:55:56,582
[ Scully ] Two more outs to
go, and here's Jesus Cabrillo,

1532
01:55:56,665 --> 01:56:00,627
who struck out
and flied to center.

1533
01:56:00,711 --> 01:56:04,506
It's been over 40 years
that I sat at Yankee Stadium...

1534
01:56:04,631 --> 01:56:09,845
and broadcast the perfect game
by Don Larson in the World Series,

1535
01:56:09,970 --> 01:56:13,974
and now I never thought
I'd be able to see another one,

1536
01:56:14,099 --> 01:56:19,271
especially from a 40-year-old pitcher who
may very well be at the end of his career.

1537
01:56:19,354 --> 01:56:21,565
Gus, goddamn it.

1538
01:56:21,690 --> 01:56:23,650
Gus, just hold it
over the middle of the plate.

1539
01:56:23,775 --> 01:56:26,195
I'm just throwin'
straight shit right now.

1540
01:56:31,867 --> 01:56:33,786
[ Scully ]
Big swing and the count 0 and 1.

1541
01:56:33,869 --> 01:56:37,623
What are you swingin' at? That
was a ball. This guy's a bum!

1542
01:56:37,706 --> 01:56:41,418
[ Groans ]

1543
01:56:51,553 --> 01:56:54,723
[ Scully ]
There's a drive down the line.

1544
01:56:54,848 --> 01:56:57,768
Foul!
What a scramble up there.

1545
01:56:57,893 --> 01:57:00,020
What used to be
just a souvenir...

1546
01:57:00,145 --> 01:57:04,566
might very well turn out
to be a very valuable baseball.

1547
01:57:05,984 --> 01:57:09,530
[ Booing ]
Oh, God.

1548
01:57:09,655 --> 01:57:12,199
[ Chapel ]
Yeah, I know, I'm stallin'.

1549
01:57:12,324 --> 01:57:16,120
Everybody knows I'm stallin'.

1550
01:57:16,245 --> 01:57:17,830
[ Booing ]

1551
01:57:17,913 --> 01:57:20,415
Maybe you'd be stallin' too.

1552
01:57:36,098 --> 01:57:38,433
[ Scully ] And there's a
strike three call. Strike!

1553
01:57:38,559 --> 01:57:42,813
Billy Chapel, striking out Jesus
Cabrillo for his ninth strikeout,

1554
01:57:42,938 --> 01:57:44,815
and he is one out away...
Ken.

1555
01:57:44,940 --> 01:57:46,483
from the perfect game.

1556
01:57:46,608 --> 01:57:49,778
- Wreck it.
- All right, skip.

1557
01:57:49,903 --> 01:57:53,115
[ Scully ]
On deck is young ken Strout,

1558
01:57:53,198 --> 01:57:56,743
who will take
his swings for Jaime Ruiz.

1559
01:57:56,827 --> 01:58:02,332
[ Man On P.A.] Batting for
Ruiz, number 60, ken Strout.

1560
01:58:11,300 --> 01:58:13,302
Why not?

1561
01:58:13,385 --> 01:58:17,723
[ Lyons ] This is a great move
by Bobby Mack, the Yankee skipper,

1562
01:58:17,806 --> 01:58:20,767
sendin'a kid up, ken Strout,
his first major league at bat.

1563
01:58:20,851 --> 01:58:23,729
He's just young enough and just
cocky enough to not realize...

1564
01:58:23,812 --> 01:58:26,398
the magnitude of
the situation that he's in.

1565
01:58:30,152 --> 01:58:33,155
[ Scully ] There's a line
drive down the right field line,

1566
01:58:33,238 --> 01:58:36,200
hooking foul!

1567
01:58:36,325 --> 01:58:41,205
And that was too close for comfort
for the Tigers and for Billy Chapel.

1568
01:58:44,333 --> 01:58:49,671
Well, I don't scare you
at all, do I, Strout?

1569
01:58:49,755 --> 01:58:52,174
Guess you forgot who I am.

1570
01:58:55,135 --> 01:58:58,680
[ Chuckles ]
Oh, God.

1571
01:58:58,806 --> 01:59:01,391
Think Billy.
Don't just throw.

1572
01:59:01,517 --> 01:59:03,393
Think.

1573
01:59:06,814 --> 01:59:11,276
No, a curveball's for shit.
He knows it. I know it.

1574
01:59:15,197 --> 01:59:17,741
He knows it.

1575
01:59:19,326 --> 01:59:21,745
This is gonna hurt
a little bit.

1576
01:59:22,913 --> 01:59:24,832
[ Groans ]

1577
01:59:24,915 --> 01:59:27,543
Strike two! [ Scully
] What's that old line?

1578
01:59:27,668 --> 01:59:31,672
"If you can keep your head when
all about you are losing theirs,

1579
01:59:31,797 --> 01:59:33,423
you don't understand
the situation. "

1580
01:59:33,549 --> 01:59:37,553
That's kenny Strout right now as he takes
another strike. The count is 0 and 2.

1581
01:59:37,678 --> 01:59:41,932
And with a weary body
and, no doubt, a sore arm,

1582
01:59:42,057 --> 01:59:46,562
now this big crowd, over 56,000,
rooting for Billy Chapel...

1583
01:59:46,687 --> 01:59:48,856
to do the near impossible.

1584
01:59:50,566 --> 01:59:55,654
It's either gonna be
your night, kid, or mine.

1585
01:59:55,737 --> 01:59:58,657
[ Scully ] Will this be
the last pitch of the game?

1586
01:59:58,740 --> 02:00:02,494
Will this be the last pitch
in Billy Chapel's life?

1587
02:00:02,578 --> 02:00:06,165
Will it be the end of his
brilliant major league career?

1588
02:00:06,248 --> 02:00:08,667
And if so, what a high note!

1589
02:00:08,750 --> 02:00:11,587
0 and 2, the count
to kenny Strout.

1590
02:00:26,268 --> 02:00:28,103
Come on, Billy.

1591
02:00:44,119 --> 02:00:47,956
[ Scully ] High bouncer
off the glove of Chapel!

1592
02:01:06,475 --> 02:01:10,687
- He's out!
- [ Scully ] He has done it.

1593
02:01:10,813 --> 02:01:14,942
Billy Chapel has
pitched a perfect game.

1594
02:01:15,067 --> 02:01:19,822
The cathedral that is Yankee
Stadium belongs to a Chapel.

1595
02:01:39,007 --> 02:01:42,636
He was safe!
Ah, geez.

1596
02:01:42,761 --> 02:01:47,808
Nice job, Chapel.
Got to give it to ya. Nice job.

1597
02:01:47,933 --> 02:01:50,185
Come on. Perfect game.

1598
02:02:11,832 --> 02:02:15,627
I told ya, Billy!
Didn't I tell ya?

1599
02:02:15,711 --> 02:02:18,714
History, man!

1600
02:02:38,066 --> 02:02:41,403
All right. All right.
All right.

1601
02:02:41,528 --> 02:02:44,990
Oh, geez. You're
the cream in my coffee.

1602
02:02:45,073 --> 02:02:49,203
Ow! That's okay.
That's okay. You didn't know.

1603
02:02:49,328 --> 02:02:52,164
This is good right here. I'll just
stay right here. Come on, come on.

1604
02:02:52,247 --> 02:02:55,459
This is a good spot. Wait.
I gotta make a phone call.

1605
02:02:55,584 --> 02:03:00,214
Well, this is
- Where are we? Oh, all right.

1606
02:03:00,297 --> 02:03:03,091
All right. Oh!

1607
02:03:04,218 --> 02:03:06,595
[ Grunts ]

1608
02:03:06,678 --> 02:03:08,847
You need anything?

1609
02:03:08,931 --> 02:03:11,433
Some water.

1610
02:03:18,357 --> 02:03:20,400
Thank you, Chappie.

1611
02:03:20,484 --> 02:03:23,278
No problem.

1612
02:03:23,362 --> 02:03:27,825
No, no, not for the water.

1613
02:03:34,206 --> 02:03:35,415
I know.

1614
02:03:37,668 --> 02:03:39,586
Okay.

1615
02:03:46,635 --> 02:03:48,679
[ Door Closes ]

1616
02:04:05,529 --> 02:04:08,907
[ Phone Beeps,
Line Rings ]

1617
02:04:08,991 --> 02:04:11,910
[ Woman ] Hello. You've reached
the hotel message center.

1618
02:04:11,994 --> 02:04:16,582
There are no new messages. Thank you
for using the hotel message center.

1619
02:04:16,665 --> 02:04:18,584
Good-bye.

1620
02:04:50,616 --> 02:04:52,534
[ Crying ]

1621
02:05:33,450 --> 02:05:35,369
Oh, God.

1622
02:07:09,463 --> 02:07:11,381
I thought you
had already gone.

1623
02:07:12,966 --> 02:07:17,763
I missed my plane. I had to
stay at the airport hotel.

1624
02:07:17,846 --> 02:07:20,140
You missed your plane?

1625
02:07:20,224 --> 02:07:22,935
There was
this ball game on.

1626
02:07:23,018 --> 02:07:25,854
You saw it?

1627
02:07:27,356 --> 02:07:29,691
With a bunch
of Yankee fans.

1628
02:07:29,775 --> 02:07:32,736
Grown men crying.

1629
02:07:32,861 --> 02:07:35,948
It was... perfect.

1630
02:07:36,031 --> 02:07:38,450
Heather saw it too.

1631
02:07:38,534 --> 02:07:43,247
I called her at school. We were
both so proud of you, Billy.

1632
02:07:49,294 --> 02:07:51,213
What are you doing here?

1633
02:07:53,549 --> 02:07:57,553
I was- I was
on my way to England.

1634
02:07:59,179 --> 02:08:01,056
Why?

1635
02:08:03,809 --> 02:08:05,769
Because you're there.

1636
02:08:13,235 --> 02:08:16,864
God, I thought
- I thought I was gonna have an ocean...

1637
02:08:16,947 --> 02:08:20,909
to think about what I wanted to
say to you, what I needed to say.

1638
02:08:21,034 --> 02:08:23,662
Billy, you don't need to. Yes, I-

1639
02:08:23,745 --> 02:08:26,081
[ Groans ]

1640
02:08:29,418 --> 02:08:32,588
jane, I used to believe-
I mean, I still do...

1641
02:08:32,713 --> 02:08:35,591
that if you give something
your all, everything you have,

1642
02:08:35,716 --> 02:08:39,428
it doesn't matter
if you win or lose...

1643
02:08:39,553 --> 02:08:42,639
as long as you risked everything,
put everything out there.

1644
02:08:42,764 --> 02:08:45,601
And I've done that.

1645
02:08:45,684 --> 02:08:50,814
I did it in my life.
I did it... with the game.

1646
02:08:53,150 --> 02:08:55,194
But not with you.

1647
02:08:56,612 --> 02:09:00,741
I never gave you that,
and I'm sorry.

1648
02:09:04,036 --> 02:09:06,663
Okay. Preboarding announcement
for Oceanic Airways,

1649
02:09:06,789 --> 02:09:10,250
flight number seven to
London. I have to go.

1650
02:09:10,375 --> 02:09:14,963
All ticketed passengers
please proceed-

1651
02:09:15,088 --> 02:09:17,341
jane. I've already missed my plane once.

1652
02:09:17,466 --> 02:09:19,802
jane, listen.
I know I'm-

1653
02:09:19,885 --> 02:09:22,179
I know I'm really
on thin ice here, but...

1654
02:09:22,304 --> 02:09:27,017
when you said
that I didn't need you,

1655
02:09:27,142 --> 02:09:29,478
well, last night-

1656
02:09:29,561 --> 02:09:34,316
